<doc id="411946" wikidata="Q1143747" url="?curid=411946" title="Automatic train protection">
<text>Automatic train protection (ATP) is the generic term for train protection systems that continually check that the speed of a train is compatible with the permitted speed allowed by signalling, including automatic stop at certain signal aspects. If it is not, ATP activates an emergency brake to stop the train.

